<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-04-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="715" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Lyon</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-04-16"><hi rend="italic">April 16,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 232.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                            Liberian commission referred to in my No. 222, diplomatic, and dated
                            January 25, 1908, consisting of Ex-president Dr. G. W. Gibson, Vice
                            President J. J. Dossen, and Attorney C. B. Dunbar, together with C. R.
                            Branch and T. J. R. Faulkner as attachés, will leave here the 17th
                            instant, via Hamburg, Germany, for the United States of America.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ernest Lyon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>